2500|$|In {{the final}} campaign, The Parish, Virgil drops the group off at New Orleans, where the {{military}} {{appears to be}} evacuating civilians across a bridge. On the way there, the four discover the city overrun with Infected, and <b>that</b> <b>the</b> <b>military</b> <b>is</b> actually leaving the city before it is destroyed by an air strike. The group manages to reach the bridge, where they {{make contact with the}} military. Judging from their dialogue, the military pilots suspect the Survivors to be [...] "carriers", similar to the original Survivors of Left 4 Dead. After securing their rescue helicopter, the Survivors lower and cross the bridge, escaping on the helicopter just as the bridge is destroyed. While the Survivors' fate is left unclear after this point, Chet Faliszek, the game's writer, back in 2009 said <b>that</b> <b>the</b> <b>military</b> <b>is</b> taking survivors to cruise ships in the Caribbean in an attempt to escape the infection.|$|E
